Extension of QueryMatches representing a projection of an origin QueryMatches. An instance of this class containing a sub-sequence of tuples and the reference to the origin tuple sequence.

Method Detail

projection

private void projection(QueryMatches origin,
                        java.util.Set<java.lang.String> variables)
                 throws TMQLRuntimeException
Internal method to create the projection of the origin tuple sequence. At first the method extract all asymmetric keys of the given QueryMatches. Asymmetric keys are all keys which are not contained in the given variable set. After all each tuple will be reduced to the set of symmetric keys by removing each asymmetric key. Because of multiple instances of the same projected-tuple, each projection stores the origin tuples to enable the re-projection to the original one.

Parameters:
origin - the origin tuple sequence
variables - the set of variables to project
Throws:
TMQLRuntimeException - thrown if at least one variable is not contained by the given QueryMatches.
